1
00:00:01,390 --> 00:00:03,250
CHAPTER ONE

2
00:00:03,250 --> 00:00:10,920
The First Meeting
The train rushed along angrily. Guy was thinking

3
00:00:10,920 --> 00:00:21,160
about Miriam. He saw her round pink face,
her cruel mouth... he started to hate her.

4
00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:28,279
'Perhaps Miriam doesn't want a divorce,' Guy
thought unhappily. 'But she's pregnant and

5
00:00:28,279 --> 00:00:36,809
it's not my child, and she must want to marry
the father. Why does she want to see me, though?

6
00:00:36,809 --> 00:00:44,629
She can get a divorce without that. Perhaps
she doesn't want a divorce, only money.'

7
00:00:44,629 --> 00:00:49,969
Miriam sometimes asked him for money and he
always sent it because she was good at making

8
00:00:49,969 --> 00:00:58,180
trouble and Guy didn't want his mother to
be unhappy. In Metcalf, Guy's home town, Miriam

9
00:00:58,180 --> 00:01:04,230
pretended that Guy lived in New York so he
could succeed as an architect before he sent

10
00:01:04,230 --> 00:01:05,830
for her.

11
00:01:05,830 --> 00:01:11,920
Guy thought about his girlfriend Anne and
how much he loved her, and about the important

12
00:01:11,920 --> 00:01:22,700
job he had in Florida. He felt happy. 'Soon...'
Guy said to himself. 'Soon...' He started

13
00:01:22,700 --> 00:01:25,180
to read his book.

14
00:01:25,180 --> 00:01:32,719
After he had read half a page Guy looked up
and saw a young man sitting opposite him.

15
00:01:32,719 --> 00:01:39,150
The young man was very tall and thin, and
he smiled shyly at Guy as if he did not know

16
00:01:39,150 --> 00:01:46,659
whether to speak or not. Guy moved in his
seat and accidentally touched the young man's

17
00:01:46,659 --> 00:01:47,930
foot.

18
00:01:47,930 --> 00:01:50,240
'Sorry,' Guy said.

19
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:58,149
'That's all right,' the man said. 'Say, where
are we? Do you know?'

20
00:01:58,149 --> 00:02:00,000
'Texas.'

21
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:05,270
The young man took a small bottle of whisky
from his pocket and offered it to Guy with

22
00:02:05,270 --> 00:02:13,940
a friendly smile. He had a very large head,
his face did not look stupid or intelligent,

23
00:02:13,940 --> 00:02:23,290
or young or old. His eyes were red and tired,
but his skin was as smooth as a girl's.

24
00:02:23,290 --> 00:02:26,489
'No, thanks,' Guy said.

25
00:02:26,489 --> 00:02:34,459
The young man drank some of the whisky, then
he asked, very politely, 'Where are you going?'

26
00:02:34,459 --> 00:02:38,420
'Metcalf.' Guy wanted to read his book.

27
00:02:38,420 --> 00:02:44,500
'Nice town, Metcalf,' the young man said.
'Are you going on business?'

28
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:49,739
'Er, yes.' Guy turned the page of his book.

29
00:02:49,739 --> 00:02:55,700
'What business?' the young man asked, like
a child.

30
00:02:55,700 --> 00:02:57,340
'I'm an architect.'

31
00:02:57,340 --> 00:03:05,120
'That's interesting,' he said. He put his
hand forward. 'My name's Bruno, Charles Anthony

32
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:06,840
Bruno.'

33
00:03:06,840 --> 00:03:10,940
Guy shook his hand. 'Guy Haines,' he said.

34
00:03:10,940 --> 00:03:14,640
'Do you live in New York, Guy?' Bruno asked.

35
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:16,650
'Yes I do.'

36
00:03:16,650 --> 00:03:23,959
'I live on Long Island,' Bruno said. 'I'm
going to Santa Fe on holiday.'

37
00:03:23,959 --> 00:03:30,280
Guy wanted to read, or to think, but he could
feel this man who wanted to talk all the time

38
00:03:30,280 --> 00:03:38,750
looking at him. The train stopped and Guy
took a walk outside for some fresh air, but

39
00:03:38,750 --> 00:03:47,569
it wasn't fresh, it was hot and thick. He
went back to the train for some dinner.

40
00:03:47,569 --> 00:03:55,790
'Hello!' Bruno sat down at Guy's table. 'Look,
I've got a private room. Have dinner with

41
00:03:55,790 --> 00:03:57,829
me, that'll be nice.'

42
00:03:57,829 --> 00:04:02,439
'No, thanks. I...' Guy said.

43
00:04:02,439 --> 00:04:11,050
'Yes!' Bruno said. He stood up quickly. He
seemed drunk. He ordered dinner for two in

44
00:04:11,050 --> 00:04:16,350
his private room, then he walked away, stepping
carefully.

45
00:04:16,350 --> 00:04:24,020
Guy followed him. 'Why not?' he thought. 'He's
someone to talk to.'

46
00:04:24,020 --> 00:04:30,950
Bruno's room was very untidy. There were clothes,
magazines, cigarettes, chocolates everywhere

47
00:04:30,950 --> 00:04:38,610
on the floor and the seats. In the middle
of the floor Guy saw four big bottles of whisky

48
00:04:38,610 --> 00:04:45,560
in a straight line. A waiter brought dinner
and they started to eat, and to drink the

49
00:04:45,560 --> 00:04:46,560
whisky.

50
00:04:46,560 --> 00:04:54,200
'What are you going to build in Metcalf, Guy?'
Bruno asked, his mouth full of food.

51
00:04:54,200 --> 00:05:01,790
'Nothing,' Guy said. 'My mother lives in Metcalf,
it's my home.'

52
00:05:01,790 --> 00:05:07,270
Bruno stopped eating. 'Do you like your mother,
Guy?'

53
00:05:07,270 --> 00:05:08,300
'Yes.'

54
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:11,380
'Your father, too?'

55
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:14,070
'He's dead,' Guy said.

56
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:23,120
'Oh. Yeah, I like my mother, too,' Bruno said.
'She's coming to Santa Fe. We do everything

57
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:29,070
together.' Bruno stopped suddenly. 'Do you
think that's strange?'

58
00:05:29,070 --> 00:05:32,570
'No,' Guy said.

59
00:05:32,570 --> 00:05:39,461
'Mother gives me money,' Bruno said. He lit
a cigarette and drank more whisky. 'Father

60
00:05:39,461 --> 00:05:47,300
never gives me anything. He's rich, too!'
Bruno shouted. 'I want my own money!'

61
00:05:47,300 --> 00:05:54,030
Then Bruno laughed. 'Father would like you,
Guy. You're good and quiet, and you've got

62
00:05:54,030 --> 00:06:02,020
a good job, too. Me? I don't want to work.
Why should I? I don't feel like it.' Bruno

63
00:06:02,020 --> 00:06:11,940
laughed again. 'Father wants me to go into
his business. Like Hell I will!' Bruno pushed

64
00:06:11,940 --> 00:06:18,320
his cigarette into the dish of butter next
to his plate. 'He never gives me money - I

65
00:06:18,320 --> 00:06:28,750
know he doesn't like me. I don't like him.
You know, Guy, sometimes, I could kill him.'

66
00:06:28,750 --> 00:06:35,970
Bruno looked at Guy. 'Did you ever want to
murder someone, Guy?'

67
00:06:35,970 --> 00:06:42,830
Guy wasn't listening, he was thinking about
Anne and Miriam and Florida. It was all mixed

68
00:06:42,830 --> 00:06:44,680
up in his head.

69
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:52,830
'Tell me about you, Guy,' Bruno asked. 'What
kind of things do you build?'

70
00:06:52,830 --> 00:06:59,750
'What?' Guy tried to think. 'Oh, houses, offices...'

71
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:02,060
Are you married, Guy?'

72
00:07:02,060 --> 00:07:12,040
'No. Yes. Er, well, I'm separated. I left
three years ago,' Guy said. He didn't want

73
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:14,470
to tell Bruno these things.

74
00:07:14,470 --> 00:07:17,700
'Oh? Why is that, Guy?'

75
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:19,500
'I think we were too young'

76
00:07:19,500 --> 00:07:27,190
'Do you love her?' Bruno's eyes weren't tired
now. They were bright and looked straight

77
00:07:27,190 --> 00:07:33,190
at Guy. 'You take love seriously, don't you,
Guy?'

78
00:07:33,190 --> 00:07:35,540
Guy didn't answer this.

79
00:07:35,540 --> 00:07:40,310
'What kind of girl is your wife?' Bruno asked.

80
00:07:40,310 --> 00:07:50,300
'She's pretty, red hair, a little fat,' Guy
said. 'We're going to get a divorce,' he said.

81
00:07:50,300 --> 00:07:57,450
'Why? Why now? Why not before?' Bruno's eyes
were very bright.

82
00:07:57,450 --> 00:08:03,280
'She's pregnant,' Guy said. He didn't like
saying it.

83
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:09,840
'Oh, boy!' Bruno said. 'I hate women like
that, don't you?'

84
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:15,940
'Well, no... I,' Guy said. 'It happens.'

85
00:08:15,940 --> 00:08:23,070
Bruno pulled the cigarette in and out of the
butter. 'Men go to women like her like flies

86
00:08:23,070 --> 00:08:27,320
go to rubbish,' he said. 'What's her name?'

87
00:08:27,320 --> 00:08:36,490
'Miriam, Miriam Joyce.' Guy tried to change
the subject. 'Well, Bruno,' he said. 'If you

88
00:08:36,490 --> 00:08:39,940
don't want to work, what do you want to do?'

89
00:08:39,940 --> 00:08:48,760
'I think a man needs to try everything once.
You know, everything - travel, and women,

90
00:08:48,760 --> 00:08:56,080
and, uh, robbery... and murder.' He stopped
and looked at Guy with a worried face. 'Did

91
00:08:56,080 --> 00:09:00,510
you ever want to kill someone, Guy?'

92
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:04,740
'No.' Guy was starting to feel drunk.

93
00:09:04,740 --> 00:09:11,260
Bruno picked up another bottle of whisky and
tried to open it. 'You know, Guy, the police

94
00:09:11,260 --> 00:09:18,311
don't catch most murderers.' He was very drunk
and the top of the bottle flew off. Whisky

95
00:09:18,311 --> 00:09:20,480
went all over the floor.

96
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:22,640
'Really?' Guy said.

97
00:09:22,640 --> 00:09:31,100
'No, they don't.' Bruno drank from the bottle.
'Come to Santa Fe with me, Guy! I like you!'

98
00:09:31,100 --> 00:09:38,300
'I can't,' Guy said 'After Metcalf, I have
to go to Florida. I'm going to build a sports

99
00:09:38,300 --> 00:09:39,900
club there.'

100
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:48,560
'Oh, Guy!' Bruno looked at him the way a little
boy looks at his father. 'That's great. You

101
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:51,550
must be very good.'

102
00:09:51,550 --> 00:09:54,880
Guy smiled, 'Well, thanks'

103
00:09:54,880 --> 00:10:03,020
'But,' Bruno said, 'if Miriam makes trouble
now - about the divorce - if she came to Florida,

104
00:10:03,020 --> 00:10:07,890
Guy, well, you could lose the job, couldn't
you?'

105
00:10:07,890 --> 00:10:13,090
Guy thought, 'That's the kind of thing Miriam
would do.'

106
00:10:13,090 --> 00:10:17,420
'You could murder her for that, couldn't you,
Guy?'

107
00:10:17,420 --> 00:10:19,100
'No,' he said.

108
00:10:19,100 --> 00:10:26,120
'I could make a plan for murdering your wife,
Guy,' Bruno said. 'You might want to use it

109
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,500
some time.'

110
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:28,580
'No!'

111
00:10:28,580 --> 00:10:36,990
'Oh, Guy!' Bruno stood up suddenly and waved
the bottle about. 'Oh!' he shouted. 'Guy!

112
00:10:36,990 --> 00:10:45,370
I just thought. Oh, yes! You murder my father
and I'll murder Miriam. The police will never

113
00:10:45,370 --> 00:10:56,930
find us. We're strangers, we met on a train
and nobody knows we're friends. It's perfect.'

114
00:10:56,930 --> 00:11:04,160
Now the room was a little Hell. It was very
hot, Bruno's face was red and his mouth was

115
00:11:04,160 --> 00:11:07,580
wide open, shouting, shouting.

116
00:11:07,580 --> 00:11:14,980
'No, no!' Guy said. He ran out of the room,
then he opened one of the windows and breathed

117
00:11:14,980 --> 00:11:18,410
in the cold night air.

118
00:11:18,410 --> 00:11:27,670
'Guy?' Bruno stood behind him and put his
hand on Guy's back. 'I'm sorry.' Guy pulled

119
00:11:27,670 --> 00:11:34,370
away from him. 'Oh, please, Guy.' He was like
a dog.

120
00:11:34,370 --> 00:11:38,870
'It's all right,' Guy said. 'Let's forget
it.'

121
00:11:38,870 --> 00:11:43,760
'OK, thanks.' Bruno smiled. 'Do you want another
drink?'

122
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:48,920
'No, I'm going to bed,' Guy said.

123
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:55,040
Before he went to sleep, Guy remembered that
his book was still in Bruno's room. He didn't

124
00:11:55,040 --> 00:12:02,720
go back for it. He never wanted to see Bruno
again.

125
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:09,340
CHAPTER TWO
A Difficult Day with Miriam

126
00:12:09,340 --> 00:12:15,740
When he got to Metcalf Guy phoned Miriam and
they met outside their old school. It was

127
00:12:15,740 --> 00:12:23,160
a hot day and Miriam wore a big white hat.
Her face looked fatter than Guy remembered

128
00:12:23,160 --> 00:12:26,450
and there were little lines under her eyes.

129
00:12:26,450 --> 00:12:33,580
'Hello, Guy,' Miriam said and smiled, but
shut her little mouth quickly to hide her

130
00:12:33,580 --> 00:12:38,670
bad front teeth. She looked soft and sticky.

131
00:12:38,670 --> 00:12:45,960
'Hello, Miriam,' he said. 'How are you? When
will the child come?'

132
00:12:45,960 --> 00:12:49,060
'January,' she said.

133
00:12:49,060 --> 00:12:56,760
'She's two months' pregnant,' Guy thought.
He said, 'You must want to marry him... the

134
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:57,900
man?'

135
00:12:57,900 --> 00:13:03,590
'You see,' she said, 'it's a bit difficult.'

136
00:13:03,590 --> 00:13:05,410
'Difficult?'

137
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:13,890
'He's married, Guy.' Miriam was looking in
front of her, speaking as if he wasn't there.

138
00:13:13,890 --> 00:13:17,700
'But we can still get divorced,' he said.

139
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:24,620
'Owen can't get divorced until September,
that's four months,' Miriam told him.

140
00:13:24,620 --> 00:13:28,510
'We could get divorced now,' Guy said.

141
00:13:28,510 --> 00:13:35,930
'Could we wait?' she asked. 'I think I'd like
to go away for a few months.'

142
00:13:35,930 --> 00:13:37,860
'What do you mean?'

143
00:13:37,860 --> 00:13:45,780
'Your mother told me about your job in Florida,'
Miriam said with her little smile. She looked

144
00:13:45,780 --> 00:13:53,940
up at Guy with her dead eyes. 'I want to come
with you, and stay until December.'

145
00:13:53,940 --> 00:13:59,220
'No,' he said. 'You can't do that.'

146
00:13:59,220 --> 00:14:04,390
'If you don't take me with you, I'll come
alone,' she said.

147
00:14:04,390 --> 00:14:07,339
'Then I won't take the job.'

148
00:14:07,339 --> 00:14:15,070
'You won't do that,' she said in a hard voice.
'The job's too important.'

149
00:14:15,070 --> 00:14:19,940
She loved arguing so Guy decided to be very
calm.

150
00:14:19,940 --> 00:14:24,300
'Yes, Miriam, I will,' he said.

151
00:14:24,300 --> 00:14:29,580
'Go on then,' she said. 'Run away from everything.'

152
00:14:29,580 --> 00:14:37,450
He tried to talk to her. 'Is there anything
we can do about this, Miriam?' he asked.

153
00:14:37,450 --> 00:14:42,330
'I've said what I want.'

154
00:14:42,330 --> 00:14:43,330
***

155
00:14:43,330 --> 00:14:48,100
When Guy got back to his mother's house he
found a letter from Anne:

156
00:14:48,100 --> 00:14:54,500
What's happened? Write immediately, or phone.
I want to be with you. Why don't you come

157
00:14:54,500 --> 00:15:01,410
to Mexico for a few days? Oh Guy, I'll miss
you when you're away in Florida, but I'm so

158
00:15:01,410 --> 00:15:09,070
proud of you. Mum and Dad are, too. I know
everything will be all right soon.

159
00:15:09,070 --> 00:15:13,130
All my love, Anne

160
00:15:13,130 --> 00:15:18,750
After he read Anne's letter, Guy wrote to
Mr Brillhart at the sports' club in Florida

161
00:15:18,750 --> 00:15:22,480
and said he could not take the job.

162
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:28,660
He spent the next day with his mother. That
night someone rang him on the phone.

163
00:15:28,660 --> 00:15:34,899
'Hallo,' a man's voice said. 'It's Charley.'
He sounded drunk.

164
00:15:34,899 --> 00:15:39,170
'Charley who?' Guy asked.

165
00:15:39,170 --> 00:15:42,200
'Bruno! Charley Bruno!'

166
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:46,370
'Oh,' Guy said, 'Hello.'

167
00:15:46,370 --> 00:15:52,000
'I've got your book, Guy,' Bruno said. 'Do
you want me to send it to you?'

168
00:15:52,000 --> 00:15:53,000
'Yes.'

169
00:15:53,000 --> 00:16:00,660
'Oh, I know,' Bruno said. 'Come to Santa Fe
and see me. Come now.'

170
00:16:00,660 --> 00:16:03,330
'I can't,' Guy said.

171
00:16:03,330 --> 00:16:09,980
'Okay. What about in Florida?' Bruno asked.
'I'll come and see you there. We'll have a

172
00:16:09,980 --> 00:16:11,589
great time.'

173
00:16:11,589 --> 00:16:15,730
'No,' Guy said. 'That's all finished.'

174
00:16:15,730 --> 00:16:25,051
'Why?' Bruno asked. Then his voice changed.
'Your wife, huh? I know, she wanted to go

175
00:16:25,051 --> 00:16:28,070
to Florida with you.'

176
00:16:28,070 --> 00:16:33,130
This surprised Guy. How did Bruno know these
things so quickly?

177
00:16:33,130 --> 00:16:41,120
'You can still get a divorce, can't you, Guy?'
Bruno asked. 'Guy?... Guy?'

178
00:16:41,120 --> 00:16:45,410
'Look, I have to go,' Guy said.

179
00:16:45,410 --> 00:16:56,731
'Guy, if you want me to do anything, you know,
do anything, all you have to do is say.' Bruno's

180
00:16:56,731 --> 00:17:00,850
voice was thick and slow with whisky now.

181
00:17:00,850 --> 00:17:10,100
Guy remembered Bruno's plan. He said angrily,
'I don't want anything from you. Understand?'

182
00:17:10,100 --> 00:17:15,510
'Oh, Guy!' Bruno started to cry.

183
00:17:15,510 --> 00:17:20,530
Guy put the phone down.

184
00:17:20,530 --> 00:17:25,679
CHAPTER THREE
Good News for Guy

185
00:17:25,679 --> 00:17:31,910
Guy was walking with Anne in Mexico City.
In her long white dress and with her yellow

186
00:17:31,910 --> 00:17:36,500
hair she seemed to be made of gold.

187
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:44,000
'But did you have to refuse the job in Florida
because of Miriam?' Anne asked.

188
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:48,510
'Yes. I hate her,' Guy said.

189
00:17:48,510 --> 00:17:56,710
'Guy, you shouldn't hate people,' Anne said.
'You're talking like a child.'

190
00:17:56,710 --> 00:18:03,480
He felt ashamed of what he said. Anne frightened
him when she spoke like this. She seemed so

191
00:18:03,480 --> 00:18:12,390
far away from him. She was calm and rich and
clever and happy. Guy was not used to this.

192
00:18:12,390 --> 00:18:19,929
Sometimes, when he was unhappy, Guy thought
he was the only problem in Anne's life.

193
00:18:19,929 --> 00:18:25,300
They walked some more then Anne went back
to the Ritz Hotel where she was staying with

194
00:18:25,300 --> 00:18:33,590
her parents. Guy went to his hotel. It was
an ugly place, but Guy liked it.

195
00:18:33,590 --> 00:18:39,480
The next morning Guy got a telegram from his
mother:

196
00:18:39,480 --> 00:18:48,530
Miriam lost her baby yesterday. She's very
sad and wants to see you. Can you come home?

197
00:18:48,530 --> 00:18:50,330
Mama.

198
00:18:50,330 --> 00:18:55,840
The first thing Guy did was to send a telegram
to Mr Brillhart to ask if he could have the

199
00:18:55,840 --> 00:19:02,490
job again, then he rushed over to the Ritz
to see Anne. They had a drink in the bar at

200
00:19:02,490 --> 00:19:03,600
the hotel.

201
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:08,490
'Are you going to Metcalf, Guy?' Anne asked.

202
00:19:08,490 --> 00:19:12,870
'Not now, I'm too happy,' he told her.

203
00:19:12,870 --> 00:19:17,330
'Do you think Miriam will follow you to Florida?'

204
00:19:17,330 --> 00:19:28,210
Guy laughed. 'By this time next week,' he
said, 'Miriam will be nothing to me.'

205
00:19:28,210 --> 00:19:33,670
CHAPTER FOUR
Bruno Gets Ready

206
00:19:33,670 --> 00:19:40,280
Bruno sat in his mother's room at the Hotel
La Fonda in Sante Fe and watched her put cream

207
00:19:40,280 --> 00:19:42,270
on her face.

208
00:19:42,270 --> 00:19:49,130
'Charley,' she said, 'you won't do anything
stupid when I'm in California, will you?'

209
00:19:49,130 --> 00:19:57,309
'No, Ma,' Bruno said. He felt sick and his
hands were shaking, but the idea was growing

210
00:19:57,309 --> 00:20:06,950
stronger and stronger: 'I must kill Miriam
soon,' he thought, 'in the next few days or

211
