419
00:40:36,140 --> 00:40:42,589
'Wait,' Bruno said. 'You're going to kill
my father.'

420
00:40:42,589 --> 00:40:51,200
Guy looked into Bruno's eyes. They were the
eyes of a mad child. Guy felt helpless, he

421
00:40:51,200 --> 00:40:53,640
could do nothing.

422
00:40:53,640 --> 00:41:02,289
'I'll go to the police if you don't kill him!'
Bruno said, then he left the bar suddenly.

423
00:41:02,289 --> 00:41:03,289
***

424
00:41:03,289 --> 00:41:09,259
Over the next two weeks, Guy saw Bruno standing
outside his office every evening when he left.

425
00:41:09,259 --> 00:41:15,709
Then the first letter came. It was a map of
Bruno's house with a written plan for the

426
00:41:15,709 --> 00:41:23,719
murder. Guy threw it away, but the letters
came every two or three days. The twenty-first

427
00:41:23,719 --> 00:41:30,799
letter said: 'Do you want me to tell Anne
about your part in Miriam's murder? You must

428
00:41:30,799 --> 00:41:38,951
kill my father soon, before the middle of
March.' Then Bruno sent a big gun. Everything

429
00:41:38,951 --> 00:41:43,599
seemed like part of a bad play or film.

430
00:41:43,599 --> 00:41:50,180
Guy looked at his own gun. He had bought it
when he was fifteen, because it was small

431
00:41:50,180 --> 00:41:57,400
and beautiful and perfect. He held the gun
gently, and he smiled and thought about when

432
00:41:57,400 --> 00:42:00,410
he was a boy.

433
00:42:00,410 --> 00:42:05,759
Guy spent the next day with Anne in the country,
and they went to look at their house.

434
00:42:05,759 --> 00:42:08,769
'It'll be finished by March,' Guy said.

435
00:42:08,769 --> 00:42:15,170
'That's good,' Anne said. 'There'll be two
months before we get married to buy things

436
00:42:15,170 --> 00:42:16,499
for it.'

437
00:42:16,499 --> 00:42:24,640
'Do you know what...?' Guy began to say, then
he stopped and looked at Anne from the sides

438
00:42:24,640 --> 00:42:32,599
of his eyes. He wanted to tell her about Bruno's
letters and the gun, but he couldn't. He didn't

439
00:42:32,599 --> 00:42:40,789
want any secrets from Anne, but here was the
biggest secret of all. Suddenly Guy realized

440
00:42:40,789 --> 00:42:50,059
that his life was separating into two parts,
a life with Anne - and a life with Bruno.

441
00:42:50,059 --> 00:42:55,589
They went back to Anne's house and before
dinner, Guy took a walk in the garden. He

442
00:42:55,589 --> 00:43:03,459
saw the black shape of a man - it was Bruno!
Guy hit him hard and they both fell to the

443
00:43:03,459 --> 00:43:10,450
ground, but Bruno was very strong, and his
hands went towards Guy's throat. Guy wanted

444
00:43:10,450 --> 00:43:15,940
to kill him. He pushed Bruno into the grass,
fighting hard.

445
00:43:15,940 --> 00:43:20,450
Suddenly Bruno said, 'Guy, you knew it was
me!'

446
00:43:20,450 --> 00:43:26,210
'I'll kill you the next time I find you here!'
Guy shouted.

447
00:43:26,210 --> 00:43:35,739
'Oh, Guy! Kill me if you want to!' Bruno said
laughing, 'but are you ready to kill my father?'

448
00:43:35,739 --> 00:43:39,079
'I'm ready to call the police,' Guy said.

449
00:43:39,079 --> 00:43:47,819
'And I'm ready to tell Anne about you and
Miriam, and then to tell the police!' There

450
00:43:47,819 --> 00:43:53,630
was a red light in Bruno's eyes; he looked
like a hungry animal. 'I'll write to Anne

451
00:43:53,630 --> 00:44:01,559
tonight, Guy, unless you tell me you're going
to murder my father!' He turned and ran away.

452
00:44:01,559 --> 00:44:08,490
Now Guy was frightened. He waited for Bruno's
letter to Anne to arrive. He knew he couldn't

453
00:44:08,490 --> 00:44:16,029
stop it. What could he say to her about the
murder? He did want Miriam dead, he didn't

454
00:44:16,029 --> 00:44:17,029
stop

455
00:44:17,029 --> 00:44:23,269
Bruno killing her. He was guilty, too, and
his guilt was growing stronger.

456
00:44:23,269 --> 00:44:32,039
A few days later Anne phoned Guy. Her voice
was shaking and Guy knew what had happened.

457
00:44:32,039 --> 00:44:36,180
'I've had a letter, Guy,' she said.

458
00:44:36,180 --> 00:44:40,619
'Oh?' He tried to be calm. 'A letter?'

459
00:44:40,619 --> 00:44:49,869
'There's no name on the letter, Guy,' she
said. 'It says you knew about Miriam's murder.'

460
00:44:49,869 --> 00:44:56,009
'I don't understand, Anne,' he said. 'I don't
know...'

461
00:44:56,009 --> 00:45:03,170
'Guy, I won't tell anyone,' Anne said. 'But
what's happening?'

462
00:45:03,170 --> 00:45:10,619
'Nothing's happening, Anne,' Guy said, and
thought his voice sounded strange. 'Can I

463
00:45:10,619 --> 00:45:14,769
see you tonight? We'll talk about it.'

464
00:45:14,769 --> 00:45:20,549
'No. I can't,' Anne said.

465
00:45:20,549 --> 00:45:28,509
Guy felt he was losing her, and that Bruno
was everywhere. Then Guy realized something

466
00:45:28,509 --> 00:45:35,180
more: he had started lying to Anne.

467
00:45:35,180 --> 00:45:40,969
CHAPTER NINE
Guy Makes a Decision

468
00:45:40,969 --> 00:45:47,130
The next day at work Guy had a call from Douglas
Frear of the Shaw Company. He had sent the

469
00:45:47,130 --> 00:45:52,430
company some drawings for a building, and
he wanted them to give him a job.

470
00:45:52,430 --> 00:46:01,120
'Mr Haines,' Mr Frear said, 'I've had a letter
- there's no name on it - and it says that

471
00:46:01,120 --> 00:46:08,710
you knew about your wife's murder and that
the police want to speak to you.' He waited

472
00:46:08,710 --> 00:46:16,259
for Guy to speak. 'Mr Haines, I wanted to
tell you about the letter. Are the police

473
00:46:16,259 --> 00:46:18,769
still asking questions?'

474
00:46:18,769 --> 00:46:29,589
'No, Mr Frear, and I don't know who sent the
letter,' Guy said. 'I don't know what it means.'

475
00:46:29,589 --> 00:46:36,249
Then he asked, 'Mr Frear, about the job...?'

476
00:46:36,249 --> 00:46:43,519
'I'm sorry, Mr Haines, we gave that to another
architect,' Mr Frear said quickly.

477
00:46:43,519 --> 00:46:52,700
Guy went out for a drink. He was very worried.
'If I murder Bruno's father,' he thought,

478
00:46:52,700 --> 00:47:01,029
'all of this will stop. No! I mustn't think
that. But what can I do? What's the way out

479
00:47:01,029 --> 00:47:07,710
of this?' Guy drank some more and then went
home. He slept heavily.

480
00:47:07,710 --> 00:47:14,589
Early in the morning Guy woke up and felt
someone in the room. He saw the orange end

481
00:47:14,589 --> 00:47:21,109
of a cigarette burning in the dark. He knew
who it was and what he wanted.

482
00:47:21,109 --> 00:47:25,009
'Bruno?' Guy said.

483
00:47:25,009 --> 00:47:30,299
'You're ready now, aren't you, Guy?' Bruno
said softly.

484
00:47:30,299 --> 00:47:36,390
'Yes,' Guy said, and immediately felt better.

485
00:47:36,390 --> 00:47:44,599
'Mother and I are going away tomorrow,' Bruno
said. 'Do it tomorrow night. I broke the back

486
00:47:44,599 --> 00:47:52,210
door, so you can get in easily. Here's a key,
too.' Bruno gave Guy some gloves. 'You'll

487
00:47:52,210 --> 00:48:03,039
need these.' His voice shook, 'Oh, Guy, I'll
never see you again.'

488
00:48:03,039 --> 00:48:07,680
CHAPTER TEN
The Second Murder

489
00:48:07,680 --> 00:48:12,920
Guy took the train for Great Neck that night.
He had the gloves and his own small gun in

490
00:48:12,920 --> 00:48:18,999
his pocket. Bruno's gun was too big. It was
raining when Guy got off the train at Great

491
00:48:18,999 --> 00:48:25,020
Neck. There was the bus, like Bruno had said
in all his letters. Guy remembered all of

492
00:48:25,020 --> 00:48:30,140
it. At Grant Street, he got off the bus and
started to walk. There was the tree and the

493
00:48:30,140 --> 00:48:35,199
street light, and there was the white wall
of Bruno's house. Guy felt like an actor in

494
00:48:35,199 --> 00:48:38,989
a play he'd already done hundreds of times.

495
00:48:38,989 --> 00:48:44,349
Guy walked fifteen steps along the white wall,
then he put up his hands and jumped on to

496
00:48:44,349 --> 00:48:50,519
the top of the wall. He looked down and saw
the wooden box. There were no lights on in

497
00:48:50,519 --> 00:48:56,029
the house. Guy jumped down on to the box,
landed without a sound, and ran across the

498
00:48:56,029 --> 00:49:01,089
grass towards the back door. He went up the
six white steps near the back of the house

499
00:49:01,089 --> 00:49:05,650
and opened the back door - he didn't need
the key.

500
00:49:05,650 --> 00:49:11,140
The kitchen was dark. Guy walked across it
and then went towards the back stairs that

501
00:49:11,140 --> 00:49:16,670
the servants used. Bruno had told him not
to use the house stairs because they all made

502
00:49:16,670 --> 00:49:24,789
a noise. But Guy had to be careful here, too.
He missed step three, step four and step seven

503
00:49:24,789 --> 00:49:29,530
on the back stairs because they made a noise.

504
00:49:29,530 --> 00:49:34,719
Outside the door to one of the servants' bedrooms
the floor made a noise, and at the same time

505
00:49:34,719 --> 00:49:42,660
Guy heard a clock - it was midnight. He stopped.
The servant was on the other side of the door.

506
00:49:42,660 --> 00:49:49,339
The noise of the clock went on and on - could
the servant hear? Now he remembered, Bruno

507
00:49:49,339 --> 00:49:57,279
had said, '... between eleven and midnight.'
Was this why?

508
00:49:57,279 --> 00:50:02,589
Guy felt very hot. Slowly, he opened the door
into the part of the house where the family

509
00:50:02,589 --> 00:50:03,710
lived.

510
00:50:03,710 --> 00:50:10,119
'I've been here before,' Guy thought. 'I've
done all this before. I know everything about

511
00:50:10,119 --> 00:50:16,550
this house.' Again he felt like an actor in
a play who did the same thing night after

512
00:50:16,550 --> 00:50:20,509
night. None of it was real.

513
00:50:20,509 --> 00:50:28,619
Guy closed the stair-door quietly. And there,
just there, very near, was another door - and

514
00:50:28,619 --> 00:50:35,380
behind that door was Guy's father. He walked
quietly towards the door, and slowly opened

515
00:50:35,380 --> 00:50:40,079
it with his left hand. He held his gun in
his right hand.

516
00:50:40,079 --> 00:50:46,979
The bedroom was dark, but some light came
through the window. It was only half open!

517
00:50:46,979 --> 00:50:50,260
Bruno said his father always had the window
fully open.

518
00:50:50,260 --> 00:50:56,390
'Because of the rain,' Guy thought. 'But how
will I get out?'

519
00:50:56,390 --> 00:51:02,239
Now Guy could see Bruno's father in his bed,
sleeping quietly. There was the round, dark

520
00:51:02,239 --> 00:51:05,200
shape of his head.

521
00:51:05,200 --> 00:51:08,469
'Ha-ha-ha-a!' came through the window.

522
00:51:08,469 --> 00:51:12,569
Guy shook with fear. A woman was laughing
somewhere outside.

523
00:51:12,569 --> 00:51:19,859
'This man, this man is alive,' Guy thought.
'He could laugh, too, he could... No, don't

524
00:51:19,859 --> 00:51:24,329
think. Don't think. Do it now! Do it!'

525
00:51:24,329 --> 00:51:32,049
He fired the gun. Nothing happened. It was
all a dream, all a play, nothing was real!

526
00:51:32,049 --> 00:51:40,869
Guy fired again. Nothing... He breathed slowly
and fired again. The room tore with a screaming

527
00:51:40,869 --> 00:51:48,269
sound. He fired a fourth time and the screaming
sound came again, as if the world had burst.

528
00:51:48,269 --> 00:51:54,010
'Kagh!' said the man in the bed, and his head
moved.

529
00:51:54,010 --> 00:51:59,099
Then Guy was running across the grass, but
he didn't remember how he had got there. He

530
00:51:59,099 --> 00:52:05,750
ran like a man in a bad dream who runs and
runs but cannot move.

531
00:52:05,750 --> 00:52:11,750
'You!' A man's voice shouted behind him. It
was the servant.

532
00:52:11,750 --> 00:52:14,569
Guy stood in the shadow by the white wall.

533
00:52:14,569 --> 00:52:20,940
'You!' the servant shouted again. Guy's hand
shot out and hit him on the chin and the man

534
00:52:20,940 --> 00:52:22,650
fell to the ground.

535
00:52:22,650 --> 00:52:28,719
Guy jumped over the wall, but it was very
dark and he didn't know where he was. He tried

536
00:52:28,719 --> 00:52:35,920
to be calm, then he heard a police car very
near him. The blue light moved over him for

537
00:52:35,920 --> 00:52:37,230
a few seconds.

538
00:52:37,230 --> 00:52:45,019
'Where am I?' Guy thought. 'I can't remember...
Where must I go?'

539
00:52:45,019 --> 00:52:50,479
The blue light burned his eyes. He turned
and ran away, then some trees caught him.

540
00:52:50,479 --> 00:52:55,410
The branches scratched his face and he pushed
them away with his hands, but there were hundreds

541
00:52:55,410 --> 00:53:00,979
of them. He couldn't see, he couldn't think.
He felt his own blood warm on his face and

542
00:53:00,979 --> 00:53:02,199
throat.

543
00:53:02,199 --> 00:53:07,890
Finally, Guy got out of the trees and saw
a road and the lights of a town. He walked

544
00:53:07,890 --> 00:53:14,329
slowly along the road. He still had his gun,
but his gloves were torn to pieces. They were

545
00:53:14,329 --> 00:53:20,759
probably in the trees behind him. He was too
tired to go back and look. He wanted to walk

546
00:53:20,759 --> 00:53:22,699
and never stop.

547
00:53:22,699 --> 00:53:23,699
***

548
00:53:23,699 --> 00:53:28,730
The next day Guy looked at his face in the
mirror. It was covered in scratches, and so

549
00:53:28,730 --> 00:53:34,989
were his hands. His body was heavy and tired.
He thought he could never sleep enough in

550
00:53:34,989 --> 00:53:37,029
his life.

551
00:53:37,029 --> 00:53:42,670
Guy read the papers. All the stories about
the murder said the murderer was a big, tall

552
00:53:42,670 --> 00:53:48,759
man, nothing like himself. But it said the
bullets were very small and Guy knew he had

553
00:53:48,759 --> 00:53:54,020
to throw away his gun. While he was reading,
the doorbell rang.

554
00:53:54,020 --> 00:54:03,780
'Hello, Guy. Guy! How did...?' It was Anne.
'Oh, Guy, what happened to your face? Your

555
00:54:03,780 --> 00:54:04,780
hands!'

556
00:54:04,780 --> 00:54:09,390
'A fight. It was nothing,' he said. 'In a
bar, a... Anne?'

557
00:54:09,390 --> 00:54:18,970
Anne didn't say anything for a few seconds.
'But Guy, that letter, the fight you had in

558
00:54:18,970 --> 00:54:24,650
my garden that night, and now this... What's
happening?'

559
00:54:24,650 --> 00:54:30,190
He felt frightened, then he started to cry
and couldn't stop. Anne put her hand on his

560
00:54:30,190 --> 00:54:33,709
shoulder, but she didn't try to hold him.

561
00:54:33,709 --> 00:54:42,059
'If I tell her the truth,' Guy thought, 'she'll
never touch me again.'

562
00:54:42,059 --> 00:54:45,779
CHAPTER ELEVEN
The Detective Begins Work

563
00:54:45,779 --> 00:54:52,140
Bruno sat and looked at Arthur Gerard, his
father's private detective, and thought how

564
00:54:52,140 --> 00:55:01,079
ugly he was. Gerard had a fat pink face and
little eyes, and he wore a dirty suit.

565
00:55:01,079 --> 00:55:07,579
'I'll work on this murder for nothing, Charley,'
Gerard said. 'I liked your father. I also

566
00:55:07,579 --> 00:55:09,430
think this is all very interesting.'

567
00:55:09,430 --> 00:55:14,319
'I don't care what you think,' Bruno said.

568
00:55:14,319 --> 00:55:17,289
'You hated your father, didn't you?' Gerard
asked.

569
00:55:17,289 --> 00:55:19,459
'He hated me.'

570
00:55:19,459 --> 00:55:23,859
'Tell me about Thursday night again,' Gerard
said.

571
00:55:23,859 --> 00:55:31,229
'I left Mother about 2.45 in the morning,
I went to get a hamburger, then I went to

572
00:55:31,229 --> 00:55:35,329
a bar, Clarke's,' Bruno said.

573
00:55:35,329 --> 00:55:37,849
'Nobody saw you at Clarke's,' Gerard said.

574
00:55:37,849 --> 00:55:42,349
'It was a different bar, then!' Bruno said.

575
00:55:42,349 --> 00:55:49,269
'Okay, I want to know who you spoke to,' Gerard
said. 'You see, I think it's strange that

576
00:55:49,269 --> 00:55:55,381
your father died on the night of the day you
left. I think you spoke to someone, and they

577
00:55:55,381 --> 00:55:57,380
knew you were going away.'

578
00:55:57,380 --> 00:56:02,900
'I said I don't care what you think,' Bruno
said.

579
00:56:02,900 --> 00:56:09,180
Gerard smiled. 'All right Charley. You can
go now,' he said.

580
00:56:09,180 --> 00:56:15,289
Bruno left Gerard's office angrily, but then
he thought about Guy. Gerard was too stupid

581
00:56:15,289 --> 00:56:17,160
to find out about him.

582
00:56:17,160 --> 00:56:24,039
'Guy and me,' Bruno thought, 'we're like gods.'

583
00:56:24,039 --> 00:56:27,450
The next day Gerard came to see Bruno and
his mother.

584
00:56:27,450 --> 00:56:31,890
Bruno was sitting in the garden. 'Anything
new?' he asked Gerard.

585
00:56:31,890 --> 00:56:39,640
'We found these,' Gerard said, and showed
Bruno some small pieces of the purple gloves.

586
00:56:39,640 --> 00:56:46,009
He looked across the grass. 'The murderer
ran over there,' Gerard said, 'then he got

587
00:56:46,009 --> 00:56:51,009
caught in the branches of the trees on the
other side of the wall. These pieces were

588
00:56:51,009 --> 00:56:52,019
there.'

589
00:56:52,019 --> 00:56:54,680
'Really?' Bruno tried to sound interested.

590
00:56:54,680 --> 00:57:01,259
'He knew where to go, too. The whole thing
was planned, the box next to the wall, the

591
00:57:01,259 --> 00:57:08,490
broken back door...' Gerard didn't finish.
'I'll see your mother now.'

592
00:57:08,490 --> 00:57:14,339
Bruno watched Gerard's fat body walk slowly
across the grass. He tried not to think about

593
00:57:14,339 --> 00:57:19,829
Gerard, but the man seemed to be everywhere,
and a few minutes later he followed Gerard

594
00:57:19,829 --> 00:57:21,180
into the house.

595
00:57:21,180 --> 00:57:26,970
'Do you think Charley knew about the murder?'
Bruno heard his mother ask.

596
00:57:26,970 --> 00:57:32,160
'Yes, I think so, Elsie,' Gerard said. 'Don't
you?'

597
00:57:32,160 --> 00:57:36,999
'I'll certainly tell you everything he tells
me, Arthur,' she said.

598
00:57:36,999 --> 00:57:43,499
His own mother! What if she remembered all
the stories about Guy from the paper? Suddenly

599
00:57:43,499 --> 00:57:49,920
Bruno felt alone. He wanted to sleep more
than anything, but he needed more and more

600
00:57:49,920 --> 00:57:57,059
whisky for that, and he woke up earlier and
earlier in the morning.

601
00:57:57,059 --> 00:58:02,339
CHAPTER TWELVE
The Good Man and the Bad Man

602
00:58:02,339 --> 00:58:07,839
Guy had thrown away the big gun, the purple
gloves, all the clothes he wore on that night,

603
00:58:07,839 --> 00:58:14,749
and his shoes, but he did not throw away his
own little gun. He cleaned his flat again

604
00:58:14,749 --> 00:58:20,891
and again, especially at night because he
only slept for two or three hours now. If

605
00:58:20,891 --> 00:58:26,269
he did not clean the flat, he tried to work.
He had a job to plan a hospital, but how could

606
00:58:26,269 --> 00:58:32,939
he do that with so much guilt in him, with
so much murder? He was not taking any money

607
00:58:32,939 --> 00:58:35,210
for the job.

608
00:58:35,210 --> 00:58:41,709
How could he kiss his mother again? How could
he talk to his friends? There was only Anne

609
00:58:41,709 --> 00:58:47,870
now. He still loved her, but his love for
her made him two different people. The good

610
00:58:47,870 --> 00:58:53,999
man who loved Anne and built hospitals, and
the bad man who murdered old men and helped

611
00:58:53,999 --> 00:58:57,069
to murder his wife.

612
00:58:57,069 --> 00:59:02,259
The new house was ready, and one Sunday Guy
and Anne and her parents went to see it.

613
00:59:02,259 --> 00:59:09,089
'I hear there are lots of ducks and birds
here. We could eat some,' Anne's father said.

614
00:59:09,089 --> 00:59:12,180
'Are you good with a gun, Guy?'

615
00:59:12,180 --> 00:59:17,079
They all looked round the house. It was only
a month until the wedding now.

616
00:59:17,079 --> 00:59:23,900
'We'll sit here every night as husband and
wife,' Guy thought. 'How can I do that, when

617
00:59:23,900 --> 00:59:25,430
I know the things I've done?'

618
00:59:25,430 --> 00:59:29,230
'Guy,' Anne said, 'Are you all right?'

619
00:59:29,230 --> 00:59:32,489
'Yes,' he said, and laughed too loud.

620
00:59:32,489 --> 00:59:37,559
